<subSubSection id="14BC657A6F02FFD1FF7CDED1FAC6B5EB" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5C1936F16F02FFD1FF7CDED1FC00B404" blockId="14.[151,1437,685,1900]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FF7CDED1FEDCB3D3" bold="true" box="[199,322,973,999]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae five-segmented, first and second antennomeres subequal in length; conical projection of ventral rim of pygophore bifurcate at apex; lateral angles of valvifers VIII little projected, not attaining the imaginary line connecting the mesial thrichobotria of urosternite VII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C1936F16F02FFD1FF7CD925FDB7B518" blockId="14.[151,1437,685,1900]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FF7CD925FE95B467" bold="true" box="[199,267,1081,1107]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Male.</emphasis>
Genitalia: conical projection of ventral rim of pygophore bifurcate at apex; posterolateral angles acute, medial projection of posterolateral angles directed dorsoposteriorly, attaining the level of the dorsal limit of segment X in lateral view; lateral projection of dorsal rim thin, spine like, dorsal to the posterolateral angle, and partially covering the medial projection; segment X slightly higher than wide in posterior view, and longer than wide in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FE8BD9D5FE00B4D7" box="[304,414,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[180,1404,184,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[178,1410,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pygophore of Macropygium species, ventral, dorsal, lateral, and posterior view, respectively. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–D); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (E–H); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (I–L), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (M–P, holotype). Abbreviations: cp, conical projection; lp, lateral projections of dorsal rim; pl, posterolateral angles; ppla, medial projection of the posterolateral angle; par, paramere; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 4I–L</figureCitation>
); parameres short, apical projection short and truncate, covered by long setae; largest axis of head equals half the length of stem (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FD88D9F1FD38B53C" box="[563,678,1261,1288]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,189,1556]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1437,181,1561]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paramere ventral, lateral, and dorsal view, respectively (A–L), and phallus dorsal, lateral, and ventral view, respectively (M–Y) of Macropygium species. Figure O is slightly slanted to the left to show the projection of phallotheca. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–C, M–O); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (D–F, P–R); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (G–I, S–U); Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (J–L, W–Y). Abbreviations: ap, apical projection; ds, ductus seminis distalis; mp, medial projection; ph, phallotheca; pp, projection of phallotheca; sap, second apical projection; v, vesica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692623/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 5G–I</figureCitation>
); vesica without lateral projections; ductus seminis distalis slender, middle portion twisted (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FE1FD80DFD82B518" box="[420,540,1297,1324]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,189,1556]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1437,181,1561]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paramere ventral, lateral, and dorsal view, respectively (A–L), and phallus dorsal, lateral, and ventral view, respectively (M–Y) of Macropygium species. Figure O is slightly slanted to the left to show the projection of phallotheca. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–C, M–O); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (D–F, P–R); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (G–I, S–U); Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (J–L, W–Y). Abbreviations: ap, apical projection; ds, ductus seminis distalis; mp, medial projection; ph, phallotheca; pp, projection of phallotheca; sap, second apical projection; v, vesica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692623" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692623/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 5S–U</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C1936F16F02FFD1FF7CD829FAC6B5EB" blockId="14.[151,1437,685,1900]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FF7CD829FEBBB57B" bold="true" box="[199,293,1333,1359]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Female.</emphasis>
Genitalia: Valvifers VIII longer than wide, lateral angles little projected, not covering all the basal portion of laterotergites IX, reaching the level of a line connecting the mesial thrichobotria of urosternite VII; lateral margins of valvifers VIII reaching the laterotergites VIII; laterotergites IX with mid-lateral depression (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FA8ED861FA11B5AC" box="[1333,1423,1405,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[237,1352,638,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-229@9.[225,1363,633,1865]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genital plates of Macropygium species, ventroposterior view. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (B); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (C); Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (D); Macropygium subsulcatum (Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843) (E). Abbreviations: laIX, laterotergite IX; laVIII, laterotergite VIII; vfIX, valvifer IX; vfVIII, valvifer VIII; VII, urosternite VII; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692625/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Folds of valvulae IX with few villi, conical microsculptures conspicuous; thickening of vaginal intima translucent; ring sclerites half the diameter of orificium receptaculi, this almost the width of the vaginal intima (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FB49D8D9FAD5B5EB" box="[1266,1355,1477,1503]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[215,1377,181,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[210,1377,181,1819]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Female internal genitalia of Macropygium species, ventral view. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A), Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (B), Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (C), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (D). Abbreviations: cs, capsula seminalis; dr, ductus recptaculi; er, ring sclerites; id, internal duct of the vesicular area; laIX, laterotergite IX; md, median duct of the vesicular area; vaIX, valvulae IX; vfIX, valvifers IX; vi, vagina intima; pi, pars intermedialis; pr, processes of capsula seminalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692627/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="14BC657A6F02FFD1FF7CD8F5FDA7B758" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5C1936F16F02FFD1FF7CD8F5FDA7B758" blockId="14.[151,1437,685,1900]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FF7CD8F5FED1B637" bold="true" box="[199,335,1513,1539]" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FEE1D8F6FDC9B637" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[346,599,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FEE1D8F6FDC9B637" box="[346,599,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Macropygium bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="24B176616F02FFD1FCEFD8F5FC38B637" box="[852,934,1513,1539]" name="Bolivia" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FC02D8F5FB8EB637" box="[953,1040,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1684,1708]" captionTargetBox="[172,1413,191,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[166,1420,181,1660]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distribution map of Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803), Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837), and Macropygium subsulcatum (Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692637/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), with an overlapping distribution with 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FF6BDB12FEFCB613" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[208,354,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulare">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FF6BDB12FEFCB613" box="[208,354,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. reticulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FE22DB12FD80B613" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[409,542,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinolae">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FE22DB12FD80B613" box="[409,542,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. spinolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The pygophore in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FD40DB12FCEEB613" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[763,880,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FD40DB12FCEEB613" box="[763,880,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FB0EDB12FAD8B613" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1205,1350,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulare">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FB0EDB12FAD8B613" box="[1205,1350,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. reticulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FAC5DB12FF68B67F" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinolae">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FAC5DB12FF68B67F" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. spinolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bifid apex of the conical projection in the ventral rim (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FC0BDB2DFC61B67F" box="[944,1023,1585,1611]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[180,1404,184,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[178,1410,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pygophore of Macropygium species, ventral, dorsal, lateral, and posterior view, respectively. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–D); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (E–H); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (I–L), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (M–P, holotype). Abbreviations: cp, conical projection; lp, lateral projections of dorsal rim; pl, posterolateral angles; ppla, medial projection of the posterolateral angle; par, paramere; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
), and by the slender segment X with subparallel lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FE6FDB49FDA0B644" box="[468,574,1621,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[180,1404,184,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[178,1410,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pygophore of Macropygium species, ventral, dorsal, lateral, and posterior view, respectively. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–D); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (E–H); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (I–L), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (M–P, holotype). Abbreviations: cp, conical projection; lp, lateral projections of dorsal rim; pl, posterolateral angles; ppla, medial projection of the posterolateral angle; par, paramere; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 4I, J</figureCitation>
). The conical projection and the segment X in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FBE0DB4AFB48B65B" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" box="[1115,1238,1622,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FBE0DB4AFB48B65B" box="[1115,1238,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FB5CDB49FAF4B644" box="[1255,1386,1621,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[180,1404,184,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[178,1410,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pygophore of Macropygium species, ventral, dorsal, lateral, and posterior view, respectively. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–D); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (E–H); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (I–L), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (M–P, holotype). Abbreviations: cp, conical projection; lp, lateral projections of dorsal rim; pl, posterolateral angles; ppla, medial projection of the posterolateral angle; par, paramere; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 4M, N</figureCitation>
) are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FEB7DB66FE17B6A7" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[268,393,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FEB7DB66FE17B6A7" box="[268,393,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FE5FDB66FDC1B6A7" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" box="[484,607,1658,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FE5FDB66FDC1B6A7" box="[484,607,1658,1683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lateral projections of the dorsal rim are broad and placed apart from the posterolateral angles of the pygophore (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FD3EDB81FD7FB683" box="[645,737,1693,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[180,1404,184,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[178,1410,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pygophore of Macropygium species, ventral, dorsal, lateral, and posterior view, respectively. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–D); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (E–H); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (I–L), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (M–P, holotype). Abbreviations: cp, conical projection; lp, lateral projections of dorsal rim; pl, posterolateral angles; ppla, medial projection of the posterolateral angle; par, paramere; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 4O</figureCitation>
), while spine-like and close to the posterolateral angles in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FAC5DB82FF73B6EF" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FAC5DB82FF73B6EF" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FF47DBDDFEC9B6EF" box="[252,343,1729,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[180,1404,184,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[178,1410,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pygophore of Macropygium species, ventral, dorsal, lateral, and posterior view, respectively. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A–D); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (E–H); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (I–L), Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (M–P, holotype). Abbreviations: cp, conical projection; lp, lateral projections of dorsal rim; pl, posterolateral angles; ppla, medial projection of the posterolateral angle; par, paramere; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692621/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 4K</figureCitation>
). Female genital plates in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FDC6DBDEFD66B6EF" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[637,760,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FDC6DBDEFD66B6EF" box="[637,760,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FC21DBDEFBB2B6EF" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[922,1068,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulare">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FC21DBDEFBB2B6EF" box="[922,1068,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. reticulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FBD8DBDEFB79B6EF" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[1123,1255,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinolae">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FBD8DBDEFB79B6EF" box="[1123,1255,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. spinolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as discussed in the comments made to 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FE27DBFAFDB0B6CB" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[412,558,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulare">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FE27DBFAFDB0B6CB" box="[412,558,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. reticulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The valvifers VIII in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FC97DBFAFC36B6CB" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[812,936,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FC97DBFAFC36B6CB" box="[812,936,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are narrower than 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FBC7DBFAFA9FB6CB" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[1148,1281,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinolae">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FBC7DBFAFA9FB6CB" box="[1148,1281,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. spinolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not covering the limits between the laterotergites VIII and IX (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FD04DA15FCA6B717" box="[703,824,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[237,1352,638,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-229@9.[225,1363,633,1865]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genital plates of Macropygium species, ventroposterior view. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (B); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (C); Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (D); Macropygium subsulcatum (Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843) (E). Abbreviations: laIX, laterotergite IX; laVIII, laterotergite VIII; vfIX, valvifer IX; vfVIII, valvifer VIII; VII, urosternite VII; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692625/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 6B, C</figureCitation>
). The valvifers VIII in 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FB81DA16FB2BB717" authorityName="Silva &amp; Campos" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Westwood" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[1082,1205,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidum">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FB81DA16FB2BB717" box="[1082,1205,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. bifidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are relatively longer than 
<taxonomicName id="9BA64D726F02FFD1FF75DA32FEC1B773" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[206,351,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Macropygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulare">
<emphasis id="6ED2EAE36F02FFD1FF75DA32FEC1B773" box="[206,351,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">M. reticulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, surpassing posteriorly an imaginary line connecting the spiracles in laterotergtes VIII by at least twice the spiracle diameter (
<figureCitation id="C49D2A746F02FFD1FE68DA4DFDB2B758" box="[467,556,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[237,1352,638,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-229@9.[225,1363,633,1865]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genital plates of Macropygium species, ventroposterior view. Macropygium reticulare (Fabricius, 1803) (A); Macropygium spinolae Stål, 1860 (B); Macropygium bifidum (Westwood, 1837) (C); Macropygium graziae Silva &amp; Campos, sp. nov. (D); Macropygium subsulcatum (Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843) (E). Abbreviations: laIX, laterotergite IX; laVIII, laterotergite VIII; vfIX, valvifer IX; vfVIII, valvifer VIII; VII, urosternite VII; X, segment X." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692625/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="619">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
).
